    "name": "Mike Palm (3)",
    "profile": "Mike Palm is a record label owner, producer and musician from Auburn Hills, Michigan who was active from the mid-1990's to the early 2000's. In 1995 he founded the record label [l=Five Finger Records], which was in operation for just over a year and released an album by [a=Lazy Eye Speech Community] and a demo tape by [a=Small Brown Bike]. Palm then changed his record label's name to [l=Salinger Press] in 1997. Through Salinger, he released material by [a=Small Brown Bike], [a=Dead Season], [a=Keleton DMD], [a=Lovesick (3)] and [a=Quixote (2)].\r\n\r\nHe engineered and eventually produced the bands he worked with (especially Small Brown Bike and Dead Season) at [l=Woodshed Studios, Detroit], and ultimately operated his own home studio, Backwoods Studio, from 2002 to 2004. Palm folded Salinger Press in the summer of 2000 in order to focus solely on the metal band he fronted, [a=End It]. End It remained active for over three years, until the quitting of Palm, which lead the remaining members",
